            <fr:title text="ヨよ木 (Yoyogi)">ヨよ木 (Yoyogi)</fr:title>
            <fr:meta name="orcid">0009-0008-0934-6821</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>I am Yve Meng. This is my personal website, realised as a <fr:link href="https://www.forester-notes.org/index/index.xml" type="external">forester space</fr:link>.</html:p><html:p>I am a <html:em>Quantitative Researcher</html:em> in <fr:link href="https://www.mediobanca.com/en/index.html" type="external">Mediobanca</fr:link> in London. I am also a <html:em>Research Assistant</html:em> in <fr:link href="https://thalesians.com/" type="external">Thalesians</fr:link>. I hold degrees from Cambridge and Imperial.</html:p><html:p>I study foundations of stochastic analysis using category theory, game theory and differential geometry as a guide. My other interests include linguistics, programming languages, molecular anthropology and electoral system researches. Outside professional realms, I am also interested in mathematical music theory, rhythm game designs, composing, arranging and DJ-ing.</html:p><html:p>You may find more information about me in my <fr:link href="/sezryo/" title="Yve Meng" uri="https://sez.moe/sezryo/" display-uri="sezryo" type="local">bio</fr:link>, or directly <fr:link href="/0006/" title="Contact me" uri="https://sez.moe/0006/" display-uri="0006" type="local">contact me</fr:link> for further discussions.</html:p><html:p>You may navigate this whole <fr:link href="https://www.forester-notes.org/index/index.xml" type="external">forester</fr:link> via <html:code>ctrl+K</html:code>.</html:p>
  
  <fr:tree show-metadata="false" numbered="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:uri>https://sez.moe/0001/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>0001</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/0001/</fr:route><fr:title text="Name of this website">Name of this website</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>The name ヨよ木 comes as a homonym of 代々木, a vibrant area in Tokyo. ヨ mimics the existence quantifier, よ is identified as the Yoneda functor, and 木 marks a place for inhabitance.</html:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>

  
  

  <fr:tree show-metadata="false" expanded="false" numbered="true"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:uri>https://sez.moe/0003/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>0003</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/0003/</fr:route><fr:title text="Blog">Blog</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>This is my personal blog. I also publish <fr:link href="/000F/" title="Weeknotes" uri="https://sez.moe/000F/" display-uri="000F" type="local">weekly notes</fr:link>.</html:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
  <fr:tree show-metadata="false" expanded="false" numbered="true"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:uri>https://sez.moe/0008/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>0008</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/0008/</fr:route><fr:title text="Research">Research</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>My research interest spans from stochastic analysis, mathematical finance to category theory and mathematical logic. In particular, I focus on various approaches that postulate a clearer foundational framework for modern stochastic analysis. Some topics that I have been working on includes:</html:p><fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:uri>https://sez.moe/0009/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>0009</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/0009/</fr:route><fr:title text="Markov Category">Markov Category</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>Markov category is a framework interpreting probability effects using <html:em>copy-discard categories</html:em>. Intuitively, a Markov category is a category where morphisms behave like “random functions”. This novel approach enables one to reason stocastic processes via string diagrams, similar to a relatively mature diagrammic intepretation on <fr:link href="/000D/" title="Quantum Processes" uri="https://sez.moe/000D/" display-uri="000D" type="local">quantum processes</fr:link>. A short yet clear survey can be found <fr:link href="https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/Markov+category" type="external">here</fr:link>.</html:p><html:p>I have written a set of note on Markov categories, which can be found <fr:link href="/000C/" title="Notes on Markov Categories" uri="https://sez.moe/000C/" display-uri="000C" type="local">here</fr:link>.</html:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:uri>https://sez.moe/000A/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>000A</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/000A/</fr:route><fr:title text="Hopf Algebra in Branched Rough Paths">Hopf Algebra in Branched Rough Paths</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>We try to use signature method in formalising continuous process theory in categories.</html:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:uri>https://sez.moe/000B/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>000B</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/000B/</fr:route><fr:title text="Game semantics in derivative pricing">Game semantics in derivative pricing</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:uri>https://sez.moe/000E/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>000E</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/000E/</fr:route><fr:title text="A compositional approach towards explanable AI">A compositional approach towards explanable AI</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
  <fr:tree show-metadata="false" expanded="false" numbered="true"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/sezryo/" title="Yve Meng" uri="https://sez.moe/sezryo/" display-uri="sezryo" type="local">Yve Meng</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:uri>https://sez.moe/0002/</fr:uri><fr:display-uri>0002</fr:display-uri><fr:route>/0002/</fr:route><fr:title text="Notes">Notes</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><html:p>Here assembles the collection of my typed notes. Most of them are partial and incomplete, unless otherwise noted.</html:p><html:p>These notes mainly serves for my own researching and studying purposes. Nevertheless, I'm more than happy to see if any of them inspires anyone.</html:p>
  
